<h3>Heat Management</h3>
<p>The furnace displays its current temperature. Different ores have different melting points. Temperature drops over time.</p>

<div class="tip"><strong>Infinite heating:</strong> Place an infinite lava source at the bottom of the multiblock furnace for infinite heat! Multiple lava sources stack!</div>
<div class="info-box">🌋 <strong>Lava handling, precisely:</strong> according to the local bucket docs, normal lava pouring only creates <strong>flowing lava</strong>, which disappears after a while and does <strong>not</strong> form obsidian on contact with water. A true <strong>lava source block</strong> requires <strong>Ctrl + right-click</strong> and an XP cost. Because of that, lava in this mod is genuinely <strong>loopable / refillable</strong>, not just a one-use fuel source.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🪨 <strong>Bucket of Stone:</strong> if you fall into water while carrying a lava bucket, the local item data says it turns into a <strong>bucket of stone</strong>. You can craft it back into an empty bucket, but it does <strong>not</strong> give free stone or cobblestone.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🚤 <strong>Iron Boat:</strong> the local item-doc says it can <strong>travel on lava</strong>, and when it breaks it goes <strong>back into your inventory</strong> instead of scattering like a normal wooden boat. In the active recipe set it is crafted at the <strong>Iron Workbench</strong> from <strong>5 Iron Ingots</strong>.</div>

